<H3> <TI>   Kano State Drug Agency Impounds Illegal Drugs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2802160394 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1500 GMT 
27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2802160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The zonal command of the National Drug Law 
Enforcement Agency in Kano State has impounded about 60 million 
naira worth of drugs suspected to be [words indistinct]. The 
drugs, contained in a crate, were shipped into the country from 
Singapore in a [words indistinct]. 
  Briefing newsmen in Kano, the zonal commander of the Agency, 
Alhaji Inuwa Momodou, said the crate, which was labeled 
pharmaceutical products, contained 106 cartons of the drugs 
[words indistinct]. Alhaji Inuwa stated that [words indistinct] 
drugs classified as dangerous to the human body. It is, 
therefore, unlawful for unauthorized persons to import it. 

</TEXT>

