<F P=101> BELARUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Justice Ministry Registers International Committee for Narcotics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0403112194 Minsk ZVYAZDA in Belarusian 3 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS0403112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk ZVYAZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alyaksandr Byarsudski: "CIS Steps Up </F>
Antinarcotics Movement"] 
  [Text] The International Committee for Narcotics set up in 
Minsk about a month ago by a number of public organizations from 
Belarus, Kazakhstan, Moldova, and Russia, has received a 
certificate of registration issued by the Belarusian Ministry of 
Justice. This marks the beginning of the activities of the 
committee headed by People's Deputy Viktar Piskarov, former 
interior minister. 
  The committee's working bodies comprise people who formerly 
worked in law enforcement agencies, as well as physicians and 
scientists from the four founder-states. These are different 
people but they have things in common: High professionalism and 
an understanding of the relevance of the problems to be resolved 
by the committee. 
  This is why the multifarious directions of the International 
Committee's activities include a comprehensive education 
project, and the drafting of concepts and programs on preserving 
the genetic health of the nation. The committee will be 
rendering assistance to medical and scientific institutions and 
industrial enterprises for implementing antinarcotic projects. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

