<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Antinarcotics Operations for 25 February-2 March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303024094 </F>
<F P=103> LD0303024094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
fileworthy reports on antinarcotics operations in countries 
monitored by FBIS London Bureau from 25 February to 2 March. 
Source, date and time of broadcast are given in parentheses at 
the end of each report. 
<H5>  Germany </H5>
  A 53-year-old Polish citizen in Frankfurt, Germany, was 
sentenced to five years imprisonment for attempting to smuggle 
4.7 kg of heroin. Miroslaw W., who was a chauffeur at the 
Zairean Embassy in Poland for 14 years, was taken into custody 
in July 1993 on the Polish-German border. The 4.7 kg of heroin 
was found in a suitcase supposedly covered by diplomatic 
immunity, and which was to go to Brussels. The drugs are 
estimated to have a street value of roughly 3 million German 
marks. Miroslaw W. testified that he was totally unaware of the 
contents of the suitcase, and was transporting it on orders from 
Boekwa Lokolo Okombe, councillor at the Zairean Embassy in 
Warsaw. The German prosecutors are currently preparing an 
international arrest warrant for the Zairean diplomat. (Warsaw 
PAP in English 1023 GMT 25 Feb 94) 
<H5>  Iran </H5>
  A total of 350 kgms of narcotics were seized from five drug 
gangs west of Tehran over the past 45 days by the law 
enforcement forces. Moreover, 123 smugglers and 126 addicts were 
also arrested within the same period. (Tehran IRNA in English 
1608 GMT 27 Feb 94) 

</TEXT>

