<F P=101> ARGENTINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spanish Drug Trafficker Arrested in Buenos Aires </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0903025594 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2137 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0903025594 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 8 Mar (NA) -- Personnel of the 
Argentine Federal Police Interpol Department today arrested a 
notorious international drug trafficker who was on the Spanish 
drug enforcement authorities' most wanted list. 
  The criminal is 28-year-old Tomas Moran who, after escaping 
from Spain, clandestinely entered Argentine territory in 
December 1993 to seek sanctuary in our country. 
  After a thorough investigation, Interpol Buenos Aires 
located 
Moran at a rehabilitation center for drug addicts in Buenos 
Aires Province. 
  Moran carried out his unlawful activities in the fashionable 
resorts of Ibiza and Formentera on the Spanish Mediterranean 
coast. 
  Moran is being held in custody at Interpol quarters awaiting 
a decision by the Argentine courts about his extradition to 
Spain. 

</TEXT>

