<H3> <TI>   Former President Garcia Meza Arrested in Sao Paulo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1103164594 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 1600 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1103164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Police arrested former Bolivian 
President Luis Garcia Meza in Sao Paulo this morning. The 
former president was hiding in an apartment located in a 
neighborhood close to the airport and carried a false Brazilian 
passport. He was taken into custody together with his 
aide-de-camp, Colonel Roberto Rico. Both of them had been 
charged with being implicated in an international drug 
trafficking network. Garcia Meza had been sentenced to 30 
years' imprisonment and was a fugitive from Bolivian justice. 

</TEXT>

