<H3> <TI>   Government Refuses To Relocate Medellin Cartel Members to Itagui </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1203014294 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1203014294 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alvaro Ayala from the "24 Hours Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Today, the Attorney General's Office insisted on 
relocating five Medellin Cartel members from Santa Fe de Bogota 
to Itagui. The government, however, through Justice Minister 
Andres Gonzalez, continues to resist this transfer. Today, the 
Attorney General's Office said its Medellin representative 
requested the transfer of the five people charged with being 
lieutenants of the late drug trafficker Pablo Escobar Gaviria. 
  A communique issued today by the Attorney General's Office 
states that, based on Article 35 of the Penal Procedures Code, 
the Medellin Cartel members must be accessible to the prosecutor 
in charge of their case, thereby allowing preliminary meetings 
and agreements. The government thinks differently however. 
  [Begin Gonzalez recording] Regarding their transfer, I have 
stated that, in our opinion, it is not advisable to gather the 
remaining Medellin Cartel members in the same place. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

