<H3> <TI>   Baja California Governor Questions PGR Report on Shoot-Out </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0803023794 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0803023794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jaime Flores from Tijuana from the "ACIR Radio </F>
News" newscast] 
  [Text] Baja California State Governor Ernesto Ruffo said 
today that the Attorney General's Office, PGR, report on the 3 
March shoot-out at the border is not in keeping with reality. 
He stressed that there are very strong interests behind the 
clashes. 
  Governor Ruffo said at a news conference in Mexicali, the 
state capital, that his administration will continue 
investigations even though the PGR has declared the case closed. 
  In Tijuana, Jorge Alvarez Barrieri, commander of the second 
sector of the State Judicial Police, said there are political 
motives behind the detentions and arrest warrants issued against 
members of the state judicial police as charges were fabricated 
against Deputy Prosecutor Sergio Ortiz Lara and PGR Agent Juan 
Carlos Guerrero Cermeno, both of whom have been accused of 
releasing three suspects. 
  Victor Clark Alfaro, director of the Binational Human Rights 
Center, said the judicial agents who are under arrest and those 
whose arrests have been ordered are only scapegoats and the real 
culprits have not even been mentioned. Clark Alfaro has 
demanded an investigation of State Prosecutor Juan Franciso 
Franco Rios as nobody can lift a finger without Franco Rios' 
authorization. 
  The 3 March shoot-out left four people dead, including two 
members of the Federal Judicial Police and one member of the 
State Judicial Police. 
  Deputy Attorney General Alfonso Cabrera Morales held a news 
conference on 7 March and said State Judicial Police agents were 
responsible for the shoot-out as they were protecting Ismael 
Higuera Guerrero, an assistant of the Arellano Felix brothers. 

</TEXT>

