<F P=100> CHINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qinghai Scores Counternarcotics Successes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P30035A Xining QINGHAI RIBAO in Chinese 22 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94P30035A </F>
<F P=104>  Xining QINGHAI RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Summary] Qinghai's public security apparatus has broken 
four major drug cases, seized 1.6 kg of heroin, and captured six 
drug criminals. 
  On 30 October 1993, the Xining public security bureau's 
counternarcotics team caught drug trafficker Han Defang [7281 
1795 5364] and seized .527 kg of heroin. During interrogation, 
Han admitted that two of his partners had gone to Yunnan, met 
with one Zhou Kaiqi [0719 7030 2475], and brought back over six 
kg of drugs, which they sold in Lanzhou and Xining. Public 
security cadres investigated and caught Zhou, Han Haode [7281 
1170 4104], and Han Yisi [7281 0044 0934], seizing .5 kg of 
drugs and 28,000 yuan in drug profits. 
  In January 1994, the counternarcotics team investigated drug 
trafficking in Xining by Ma Zhanzhong [7456 0594 1813]. On 4 
January, they caught him and seized .5 kg of heroin. 
Interrogation of Ma led to the 5 January capture of Zhao Zilu 
[6392 1311 4389]. Officials seized .137 kg of heroin and drug 
processing equipment and additives. 

</TEXT>

