<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> THAILAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Antinarcotics Officials Attend Bangkok Workshop </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0703044594 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0703044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] About 400 antidrug officials are gathering in 
Bangkok for two-day workshop aimed at combating the drug 
problems in the country. Deputy Permanent Secretary for 
Interior Chaloem Phromloet said the workshop will take place 
from March 7th until the 8th at the Asia Hotel, with Deputy 
Interior Minister Mr. Den Tomina presiding over the opening of 
the meeting. The participants are from Bangkok and 23 provinces 
where the drug problems have become more serious than others. 
  The Ministry of Interior has received a budget of 30.3 
million baht to its project on narcotics prevention and 
suppression in 23 provinces. The four-year project, which 
started last year, comprises six [as heard] work plans; namely, 
narcotics crop control, narcotics suppression, narcotics 
prevention, treatment of drug addicts and solving of drug abuse 
problems, and personnel administration and development. The 
workshop of the antidrug officials is expected to help improve 
the operations of the work plans in a systematic manner. 

</TEXT>

