<H3> <TI>   Van Carrying 814 Kg of Opium Seized Near Ho Chi Minh City </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0265 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0265 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] An article published on page 4 of the 21 
January Ho Chi Minh City SAIGON GIAI PHONG in Vietnamese reports 
that in mid-December of last year, the Binh Thanh Market 
Management Unit discovered a Daihatsu van which was going from 
Ho Nai to Ho Chi Minh City, carrying 18 bags containing "black 
color bars of a rather soft substance," weighing 814 kg. 
Subsequently, a lab analysis showed that each kilogram was 9.65 
percent morphine. 
  According to the local anti-drug center, based on the color, 
smell, and morphine content, the substance was actually crude 
opium. Each kilogram of the crude opium currently costs about 
$462 (5 million dong). The case has been turned over to the 
public security office for further investigation. 

</TEXT>

