<H3> <TI>   Agreement Signed With Burma To Check Drug Smuggling, Insurgency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1003093194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1003093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India and Myanmar [Burma] have signed an agreement 
on checking drug smuggling and insurgency on the border. The 
six-point agreement was signed at the end of the three-day talks 
in Imphal yesterday by Mr. H.V. Goswamy, chief secretary of 
Manipur, and Mr. (Ohn Pyne), director-general Home Affairs, 
Myanmar. The talks were held as a follow-up of the memorandum 
of understanding signed by the Government of Myanmar and India 
in New Delhi in January for the maintenance of peace and 
tranquility along the border. 

