<F P=106> [News Report: "Major Operation Against Narcotics Planned"] </F>
  [Text] Karachi (NNI) -- On special instructions from Prime 
Minister Benazir Bhutto, a major operation to clean up narcotics 
in the country is being launched. According to reliable sources, 
a sensitive agency in our country and the cooperating U.S. drug 
enforcement cell have declared the lists prepared by the former 
government to be incomplete and have expressed their 
dissatisfaction. At the prime minister's instruction, a new list 
has been prepared about the people involved in the present drug 
Mafia and its three syndicates. This list was given to the 
Narcotics Control Board after approval by the prime minister. 
According to the new list, about 200 important persons are 
involved in the deplorable drug trade, and some of them have 
already been arrested. According to these sources, important 
information about heroin factories in Ghair area have been 
collected and a major anti-narcotics operation will be launched 
within a few days. 

