<F P=106> [Editorial: "Smuggling of Heroin Chemicals"] </F>
  [Text] According to a news report, chemicals used for 
making heroin worth about one million [currency not specified] 
were "cleared" at Lahore railway station on arrival by the 
Samjhota Express from India. The intelligence agents later 
arrested the smugglers as they emerged from the railway station, 
and they have registered a case against the superintendent of 
customs. The production of heroin was initially started by the 
CIA in Afghanistan to creat money for supplying weapons to the 
forces opposing the Soviet Union. For about a decade the United 
States looked the other way. Now it considers appropriate to 
ignore all its own "actions" and prefers to accuse Pakistan of 
it. Against this background, if we review this incident of 
seizure of chemicals used in making heroin, it is clear that 
India is also involved in this drama to give Pakistan notoriety 
for making heroin. The law enforcement agencies should keep all 
this in mind and arrest the involved persons. 

