<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Reports 173 Drug Deaths in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903104694 Vienna KURIER in German 9 Mar 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> AU0903104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Peter Grolig report: "Death in the Subway: 15-Year-Old </F>
Boy Died of Heroin"] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Interior Ministry 
registered 173 drug deaths in Austria in 1993. The statistics 
have not yet been processed by the Ministries of Health and 
Justice. According to their statistics, in 1991 the police 
figures for deaths were increased from 114 to 116 and a year 
later from 146 to 187. 
  Last year the number of reports to the police on the basis 
of 
the Drug Law soared by almost 40 percent: While in 1992 7,805 
persons were reported to the police, in 1993 the number exploded 
to 10,915. The development in Salzburg was particularly dramatic 
(plus 88 percent), Tirol (plus 76 percent), and Vienna (plus 
59.8 percent). Slight declines were noted only in Carinthia and 
Burgenland. 

