<F P=101> FINLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sentences Handed Down for Heroin Possession, Trafficking </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0186A Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT in Finnish 19 Jan 94 p 
10 </F>

<F P=103> 94WD0186A </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Susanna Reinboth: "Jeweler Gets Five Years for </F>
Heroin Trafficking"] 
  [Text] On Tuesday [18 January] the members of a gang that 
had been trafficking heroin in the Helsinki metropolitan area 
were sentenced to prison terms of varying lengths. The chief 
perpetrators of the gang were sentenced two weeks ago, and now 
the dealers lower down on the scale have been sentenced. 
  The most severe sentence on Tuesday was handed down to Kim 
Christian Sjoblom, a 41-year-old Helsinki jeweler. He was 
sentenced to five years in prison for possession of over 
one-half kilo of heroin. Sjoblom had used some of the substance 
himself and had sold some. A certain amount of the substance was 
also confiscated from him. 
  The others receiving sentences on Tuesday were primarily 
heroin users. Their sentences varied from four months in prison 
to over one year. 
  According to the court, in 1992-93 Sjoblom trafficked 
narcotics that he obtained from an Espoo couple. This couple was 
considered to be the primary mover in the case, and they were 
sentenced two weeks ago. The man received nine years and his 
wife seven years in prison. 
  According to the court, this gang trafficked a total of 1.7 
kilos of heroin. Some of their drugs have been particularly 
strong and of good quality. According to Ritva Santavuori, the 
city prosecuting attorney, two persons have died because of 
overdoses from it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

