<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> ITALY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Seize 5.5 Tonnes of Cocaine From Truck in Turin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703211894 Paris AFP in English 2108 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0703211894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Turin, Italy, March 7 (AFP) -- Italian police 
confiscated 5.5 tonnes of cocaine from a truck in Europe's 
largest drug seizure yet, officials said Monday. 
  The cocaine, with a street value of around 300 million 
dollars, was found when a truck was stopped on a road in 
northern Italy overnight Saturday [5 March], police in Turin 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

