<H3> <TI>   Opium Seized in 2 Moscow Drug Busts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0803105994 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 5 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0803105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "`Gifts' From Kyrgyzstan"] </F>
  [Text] On Thursday officers of the Internal Affairs Main 
Administration Criminal Investigation Administration arrested a 
group of opium pushers. The two men, 30 and 38, citizens of 
Kyrgyzstan, together with an 18-year-old girl from Novosibirsk, 
were living in an apartment they were renting on 
Krasnobogatyrskaya Street [Moscow]. The threesome was busted in 
the actual apartment, where 1.2 kilograms of opium were stored. 
  The same day a 24-year-old inhabitant of Voronezh was 
arrested on Uralskaya Street and 600 grams of opium and a 
revolver were found in his pocket. 

</TEXT>

