<H3> <TI>   Prosecutor General Describes U.S. as `Thin-Skinned' on Drug Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1803014494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1803014494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alvaro Ayala; from the "24 Hours Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Prosecutor General Gustavo de Greiff has not let 
recent statements by U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno upset him. 
Today he indicated that the United States is too thin-skinned 
when it comes to legalizing drugs. The prosecutor general said 
that U.S. diplomatic officials visited his office and that he 
had answered U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno. [Begin recording] 
