<H3> <TI>   Arrieta `Does Not Welcome' Conflict Between De Greiff, U.S. Attorney General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1703013994 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1703013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Confidential" report by Darcy Queen; from the "24 Hours </F>
Newscast"] 
  [Text] Attorney General Carlos Gustavo Arrieta has left 
Prosecutor General Gustavo de Greiff alone in the fight 
concerning the policy over the Cali Cartel members' surrender to 
justice authorities. During an informal meeting with foreign 
journalists he said the Colombian Government does not welcome 
the fight between the prosecutor general and U.S. Attorney 
General Janet Reno. 
  Attorney General Arrieta rejected what the prosecutor 
general 
said in what represents a struggle for power that goes beyond 
Colombia's borders. In the meeting Arrieta said that the 
Colombian Government does not agree with the prosecutor 
general's position or academic views concerning his U.S. 
counterpart, Janet Reno. 
  Nevertheless, he said Reno's noncompromising attitude 
encourages solidarity with the prosecutor general, which was not 
advisable for the Colombian Government because it is concerned 
that this fight obstructs the surrender process. 
  Immediately after the meeting an Associated Press report 
said: Arrieta stated his concern that drug traffickers might 
fish in troubled waters if the confrontation continues. 

</TEXT>

