<H3> <TI>   Man Attempting To Send 600 Lbs of Marijuana to Miami Arrested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0256A Kingston THE SUNDAY GLEANER in English 30 Jan 94 p 
25A </F>

<F P=103> 94WD0256A </F>
<F P=104>  Kingston THE SUNDAY GLEANER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] After four months of 
investigation, local Narcotics Division agents arrested a 
Mandeville man on Friday on charges of possession of ganja, 
dealing in ganja and taking steps preparatory to exporting ganja. 
  He is Carlton "Carly" Dunkley, 37, businessman and former 
policeman of Westwood Apartments, Mandeville, Manchester, police 
sources say. 
  The offences were alleged to have been committed in 
September 
when two drums of what was manifested as limestone, were taken 
to the Norman Manley International Airport in Kingston to be 
air-freighted to Miami, Florida. 
  However when the drums were opened they were found to 
contain 
600 lbs. of compressed ganja, wrapped in several packages. 
Friday morning, Narcotics Division agents raided Mr. Dunkley's 
apartment and arrested him on the three charges. He is being 
held in custody to be taken before the Kingston RM Court at 
Sutton Street tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

