<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Roundup for 14-20 March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2103023094 </F>
<F P=103> BK2103023094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on narcotics developments in South Asia, Southeast Asia, 
and the Pacific monitored by Bangkok Bureau between 14 and 20 
March 1994. Source information is given in parentheses after 
each item. 
<H5>  SOUTH ASIA </H5>
<H5>  Pakistan </H5>
<H5>  Customs Seizes Hashish Near Peshawar </H5>
  Customs officials seized 7,380 kg of hashish near Peshawar 
on 
20 March. The drugs were found on board a truck travelling from 
the tribal areas near the Afghan border to Karachi. The driver 
and two accomplices were arrested. (Hong Kong AFP in English 
1406 GMT 20 Mar 94) 
<H5>  SOUTHEAST ASIA </H5>
<H5>  Philippines </H5>
<H5>  "Shabu" Dealer Arrested in Rizal </H5>
  Philippine National Police in Rizal arrested Arcadio 
Tolentino, 47, "one of the most wanted shabu dealers in Metro 
Manila and Rizal," during an 11 March sting operation. 
Tolentino was reportedly distributing drugs to different 
schools in Rizal and Metro Manila. (Manila MANILA BULLETIN in 
English 12 Mar 94 p 12) 
<H5>  Narcotics Command Arrests Drug Trafficker in Manila </H5>
  The Philippine National Police Narcotics Command has 
arrested 
a drug trafficker operating in Metro Manila. The suspect was 
identified as Alberto Palorina of Kapitolyo, Pasig. He is the 
brother-in-law of Ric Katahan, a drug lord killed by government 
authorities last year. Officials confiscated 20 grams of 
methaphetamine hydrochloride and a .22 caliber pistol during the 
raid on his house. (Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in 
Tagalog 0500 GMT 14 Mar 94) 
<H5>  Authorities Conduct Antidrug Operation in Cagayan </H5>
  Police and intelligence operatives in Tuguegarao, Cagayan 
have conducted an antidrug operation called "Operation 
Thunderbolt." They arrested a government employee caught in the 
act of selling 10,000 Philippine pesos worth of methaphetamine 
hydrochloride, and also burned about 15,000 fully-grown 
marijuana plants at a plantation in Kalinga-Apayao. (Manila 
MANILA BULLETIN in English 15 Mar 94 p B-21) 
<H5>  Thailand </H5>
<H5>  Singaporean Arrested at Bangkok Airport for Heroin Possession </H5>
  Singaporean national Tan Wun Hong Chu-eng, 25, was arrested 
with 3.700 kg of heroin at Bangkok's international airport on 12 
March. He was boarding an Ethiopian Airlines flight bound for 
Ethiopia when a team of Customs and Narcotics Suppression Police 
searched him and found the heroin hidden in his travel bag. 
(Bangkok SIAM RAT in Thai 13 Mar 94 p 3) 
<H5>  Two Italians Arrested With Heroin, Syringes </H5>
  Italian siblings Gianni Labella, 49, and Mariafia Labella, 
47, were arrested in their room in Bangkok's Metro 21 Hotel on 
11 March. Officials found 80 tubes of heroin and 23 syringes 
hidden in a clothes bag. The suspects said they bought the 
drugs in Bangkok for $3,000. (Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 
15 Mar 94 p 3; Hong Kong AFP in English 0348 GMT 15 Mar 94) 

</TEXT>

