<H3> <TI>   Police Seize 1 Kg of Heroin From Spare-Parts Dealer </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1203171094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1600 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1203171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 12 Mar (MENA)--Counternarcotics squads today 
seized 1 kg of heroin having an estimated street value of 1.5 
million pounds. 
  Information reached Maj. Gen. Mahmud Wajdi, director general 
of the Criminal Investigation Department, that Musa Kayrub Musa, 
a motor spare-parts dealer in Sulayman al-Halabi Street in the 
center of Cairo has brought 1 kg of heroin with the assistance 
of others through the Red Sea with the intention of selling it 
during the 'Id al-Fitr holiday. 
  The defendant, who is 60 years old and is considered very 
rich, confessed to possessing the heroin. He said two of his 
colleagues from Qina Governorate in Upper Egypt brought him the 
heroin. The public prosecutor began interrogating the defendant. 

</TEXT>

