<F P=100> EAST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Youths Claim Heroin Among Drugs Available in Tirana </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703175594 Tirana ATA in English 1138 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1703175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 17 (ATA) -- "Heroin and hashish can 
be found in Tirana now," some youngsters who didn't want to be 
identified told an ATA reporter. 
  According to them, a gram of heroin costs 1,000 leks and 
after buying they divide it into four parts enough to fill two 
cigarettes. 
  The youngsters said it is not difficult to notice signs of 
these drugs even in the public places. 
  Pethidine was introduced in Albania no more than two years 
ago as an indispensable medicament in the emergency wards of 
clinics and hospitals but now there are shortages of it. Time 
before it was given in pharmacies free of charge while now it 
costs 500 leks and the price may increase again. Doctors at the 
central clinic in Tirana said that there are cases when 
youngsters have threatened them in order to get pethidine. 
According to some youths, pethidine is a weak drug for them to 
be used. 

</TEXT>

