<H3> <TI>   Police Discover Amphetamine Laboratory Near Budapest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603194694 Budapest MTI in English 1546 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1603194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 16 Mar (MTI) -- On March 11, Hungarian 
police seized 15 kgs of amphetamine ready to be compressed into 
tablets, and another 30 kgs of uncleansed material at a secret 
laboratory set up in the cellar of a country house in Biatorbagy 
near Budapest. (Amphetamine is a chemically produced synthetic 
material). This has been the greatest catch in Hungarian drug 
history, the Budapest daily NEPSZAVA reported today. 
  The search followed a warning from the Swedish police of 
good-quality amphetamine being distributed near Malmo, 
presumably transported to Scandinavia from or via Hungary. 
  The drug quantity produced and distributed in Europe is 
still 
unknown. 
  A Swedish-resident Hungarian man and a Greek citizen, who 
rented the house in Biatorbagy, were taken into custody. 

</TEXT>

