<H3> <TI>   Drug Confiscations in Kaliningrad Reportedly Becoming `More Frequent' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1803151894 Kaliningrad YANTARNIY KRAY in Russian 11 Mar 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> WS1803151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kaliningrad YANTARNIY KRAY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by V. Fedorov: "Drugs Are Counted in the Hundreds </F>
of Kilograms"] 
  [Text] Cases of board and customs services in Kaliningrad 
Oblast uncovering attempts to import drugs from Lithuania have 
become more and more frequent. Things have reached the point 
that last year the customs house in Chernyakhovsk was rated 
third in Europe and first in Russia in terms of the amount of 
confiscated drugs. 
  What is the total amount of confiscated "white death?" As 
Nikolay Petrovich Iliyn, chief of the Department for Work with 
Border and Customs Services at the Oblast Administration 
Division for Public Security and Territorial Protection, has 
specified, the figure came to 387 kg in 1993. 

</TEXT>

