<H3> <TI>   Five Traffickers Arrested, 20 Kg of Cocaine Seized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0246A Buenos Aires LA PRENSA in Spanish 12 Feb 94 p 15 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0246A </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires LA PRENSA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Excerpts] An investigation by the Federal Operations 
Division of the Dangerous Drugs Office of the Federal Police led 
to the arrest of five traffickers and the seizure of 20 kilos of 
extremely pure cocaine. The operation culminated with a 
spectacular raid in the heart of the Flores neighborhood 
yesterday evening. 
  The site of these events was Calle Andres Lamas between 
Gaona 
and Franklin, where a large drug transaction was about to take 
place. 
  Forewarned, discreet police surveillance was set up in the 
area, awaiting the right moment to go into action. 
Superintendent Jorge Palacios, director of Federal Operations, 
was in charge. 
<H5>  The Roundup </H5>
  According to the police report, [passage omitted] two Ford 
Fuegos, one red and the other gray, were parked near Franklin. 
[passage omitted] 
  After the traffickers, from whom no weapons were taken, had 
been overpowered, [passage omitted] a long and painstaking 
search was made of the interior of the two Ford Fuegos in which 
the criminals had arrived at the scene. In the red car brown 
nylon bags were found, each containing one kilo of cocaine. 
Twenty kilos were found, all in bags like the ones just 
described. [passage omitted] 
<H5>  A Revealing Detail </H5>
  It was learned there that one of the two occupants of the 
red 
car in which the drugs were found is a Bolivian citizen, who had 
earlier been sentenced in Argentina to 12 and 1/2 years in 
prison. For reasons still unknown, he was released after serving 
only one and a half years of his court-imposed sentence. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

