<H3> <TI>   Prosecutor General's Office No Longer Protecting Escobar's Family </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2303023794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2303023794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alvaro Ayala from the "24 Hours Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Prosecutor General Gustavo de Greiff announced today 
that protection has been pulled from the family of Pablo 
Escobar. The prosecutor said that as of today the Prosecutor 
General's Office is no longer responsible for the security of 
the wife and children of the late leader of the Medellin Cartel. 
Alvaro Ayala has the report. 
  [Begin recording] [Ayala] The prosecutor general has 
officially announced the withdrawal of security that was 
provided by his personnel to the Escobar Henao family. He 
explained that the Army and police are the government agencies 
now responsible for this service. 
  [De Greiff] I understand that the protection was withdrawn 
as 
of today. That protection had been reduced gradually, and, as 
of today, it has been withdrawn completely. 
  [Ayala] Why did no one cooperate, and who should assume this 
responsibility? 
  [De Greiff] That is what happens to Colombia. They want us 
to supply all of the corpses and make all of the efforts, while 
other countries do not help at all. 
  [Ayala] The prosecutor general concluded by saying he never 
told the Escobar Henao family to move to the northern sector of 
Santa Fe de Bogota but that they can move anywhere they want 
because they are not wanted by the law. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

